result.execSummary:
The defendant Candice A McCampbell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superAgency.name: District Attorney
superAgency.notes: For the  period of this agreement, the defendant will comply with the following conditions:  The defendant shall notify the District Attorney's Office of any change of address or phone number within five (5) days of such change.  Def shall have quarterly contact with the Iron County District Attorney's Office via phone or letter.  The defendant shall pay any applicable attorney fees, court costs and/or assessments if she violates the terms of this agreement.  Defendant's bond conditions of no alcohol and no controlled substances remain in effect.  Prescription medication is allowed only in the amounts prescribed by a licensed physician.  Other bond conditions are dropped.  Def shall submit to random drug tests, including lab blood draws upon request of law enforcement.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is eligible for Good Time

Defendant Candice A McCampbell in court.  Joseph Hoffmann appears via telephone means on behalf of def.  Frederick j Schellgell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case and pending case.  Cites appearances.  Motion hearing today re DEJ.  Hoffmann requests continuance to allow time to speak with DA.  Court advises hearing right now.  10:37 a.m. Officer Klawitter sworn in, direct by DA.  Exhibit #1 marked by court for plaintiff.  10:40 a.m.  Cross by atty Hoffmann.  Witness released.  10:40 a.m.  Officer Samardich sworn in.  Direct by DA.  No cross by attorney Hoffmann.  Witness released.  DA moves for Exhibit #1 to be entered into the record.  Attorney Hoffmann objects as has not seen report.  Recess at 10:46 for clerk to fax report.  Back on record at 10:49 a.m.  Hoffmann admits recieving and reviwing Exhibit #1.  No objection.  Court recieves Exhibit #1.  Attorney Shellgell makes summary argument.  Hoffmann argues against motion.  Asks court to take motion under advisement.  DEJ constitutes contract, per court.  Def violated DEJ.  Imposes 30-day sentence but gets credit for time served.  Sheriff's dept to advise of CTS.  Bond motion filed by Atty Hoffmann to be rescheduled. klr
